Religious, Spiritual & Ethical Life
The MIT Gospel Choir performs at the MLK luncheon.
Health & Wellness
Succeeding at MIT means staying healthy — mind and hand, body and soul. Everyone needs a checkup or a check-in sometime. The Institute’s network of physical and mental support resources aims to keep our community happy, healthy, and active. And, through initiatives like
MindHandHeart
, we are always looking for ways to engage students, faculty, and staff to make MIT stronger and more welcoming.
